                <h1>Application of Methodology</h1>
                <h5 class="w3-padding-32">
                    <ul>
                        <li>An LXD methodology that will increase learner engagement is to be learner-centric, evidence-based and promotes continuous refinement.</li> <br>
                        <img alt="Poster" src="/images/Application_Methodology.jpg"> <br>
                        <li>A learner-centric design requires partnering with learners to co-create better learning experiences. Some micro-strategies include applying ‘learner empathy’ methods such as empathy mapping, focus groups, surveys, ethnographic
                            research and journey mapping.</li> <br>
                        <li>A design process that is backed by evidence leads to a more well-balanced learner experience design. Examples of evidence-based design include performing formative assessments, reviewing of module evaluation feedback and employing
                            data analytics when applicable.
                        </li> <br>
                        <li>Reflection and iteration using timely feedback is an important aspect of Learning Experience Design. Examples of reflection and iteration methods include Kolb’s Reflective Model. A deliberate reflective and iteration process is
                            consistent with NYP’s quality and process standard of performing module review for improvement. This process has the impact of improving an educator’s proficiency in engaging learners. </li> <br>
                        <li>The LXD Framework to be employed will put in place a structured methodology and set of checklists that facilitate and monitor the use of learner-centric design, the consideration of data and the inclusion of a reflective and iteration
                            stage in the design of learning in NYP.
                        </li>
                        <br>

                    </ul>


