                <h1>Enhancing Competencies</h1>
                <h5 class="w3-padding-32">There are two main micro-strategies in enhancing staff competencies in LXD; developing capabilities and deepening expertise.</h5>

                <div class="w3-text-grey">
                    <ol>
                        <li>To develop staff capabilities, an LXD Competency Roadmap collating necessary proficiencies to fulfil specific tasks in the LXD methodology will be developed. These specific tasks include learner profiling, setting learning goals,
                            ideation and design of lessons, delivery of lesson, evaluation and refinement. The purpose of the competency roadmap is to equip staff with the necessary skillsets through continuing professional development and train-the-trainer
                            programmes.
                        </li><br>
                        <li>
                            For staff who are already competent in their practice of LXD, they are encouraged to deepen their expertise through action research, inspire the larger T&L community through public sharing of their research or by applying LXD collaboratively with industries
